                    </zone>
                  </zone>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone forceUpdate='true' h='9333' id='15' type-v2='text' w='98770' x='615' y='90000'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>Method</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>:  Booster EV computed from MTGJSON community-maintained collation configs (print-sheet weights), with each slot priced at the weighted-average TCGplayer market price of the cards on its print sheet. Realizable EV applies a bulk floor — cards under $0.25 valued at $0.02 — reflecting that bulk commons cannot be liquidated at market price.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>Sources</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>:  MTGJSON (AllPrintings, AllPrices) · TCGplayer market prices · Sealed Play Booster prices hand-collected from TCGplayer, 2026-07-10.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>Scope</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>:  Play Booster era — MKM (Feb 2024) onward, 15 sets. Universes Beyond sets flagged separately.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>Limitations</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>:  Singles-market proxy, not Wizards of the Coast internal cost, margin, or sales data. Collation configs are community-maintained and may deviate from official print sheets. Sealed prices are a single-date snapshot; EV reflects singles prices as of that date.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>Author</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat'>:  Obie W. Lawrence  ·  github.com/obi-law</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone forceUpdate='true' h='18917' id='35' type-v2='text' w='98770' x='615' y='71083'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#edf1f6' fontname='Oswald' fontsize='12'>WHAT THE DATA SHOWS</run>
                  <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#edf1f6' fontname='Montserrat' fontsize='12'>Finding 1:</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat' fontsize='12'> The bulk discount is a constant, not a variable.  Every Play Booster carries $1.17–$1.48 of singles that can&apos;t be liquidated — a median $1.37, or 22% of nominal EV. The flip from 13/15 to 5/15 sets happens because most sets&apos; nominal margin was thinner than that fixed haircut.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#edf1f6' fontname='Montserrat' fontsize='12'>Finding 2:</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat' fontsize='12'> Licensed sets are priced above their content.  Universes Beyond packs return a median 0.79× realizable value vs. 0.93× for in-universe sets. Final Fantasy is the clearest case: the highest nominal EV of any set ($8.59) and the only pack priced above it ($9.08).</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#edf1f6' fontname='Montserrat' fontsize='12'>Finding 3:</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#8a97a8' fontname='Montserrat' fontsize='12'> Sealed pricing tracks brand more than content.  Pack prices span $3.99–$9.08 while the value inside spans only $4.41–$8.59 (correlation 0.78). Price is set by demand and licensing, not by what&apos;s in the pack.</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                  <format attr='padding' value='12' />
                  <format attr='background-color' value='#151b25' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone custom-title='true' h='4333' id='22' mode='compact' param='[Parameters].[Parameter 1]' type-v2='paramctrl' w='12231' x='1538' y='26583'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontname='Montserrat' fontsize='10'>Sort sets by:</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
